transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yeah, hi.

Speaker 1: I ordered a thing of pills from you guys one time,

Speaker 2: but you keep sending me, like every month,

Speaker 1: you send me another bottle.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but any chance were you able to look at the email

Speaker 1: that was sent to you after placing your first order?

Speaker 2: It's the terms and conditions.

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: I didn't look at that, no.

Speaker 1: Got it, no worries.

Speaker 2: So basically it just kind of explains your order a little more in detail.

Speaker 1: Since these are prescription orders through the Pfizer company,

Speaker 2: they need to have a refill date to be activated on the prescription side.

Speaker 1: So the doctor will select the refill date for you.

Speaker 2: However, you can always call us to modify that.

Speaker 1: But if you don't reach out to modify it,

Speaker 2: it will just be sent out during the time frame the doctor chose for you.

Speaker 1: I can see what he picked for you and make the adjustment now.

Speaker 2: What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 1: Rayo, R-A-O-3-4-6-5-2.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry, 3-4-6-5-5.

Speaker 1: Okay, and his first name is John, correct?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, got it.

Speaker 2: So I pulled up the right profile.

Speaker 1: All right, so I do see he has you for every month.

Speaker 2: You have basically one option I could provide for you.

Speaker 1: It's usually switching it over to our every six-month freeze plan.

Speaker 2: What that does is it still gives you access to the Viagra

Speaker 1: for when you eventually do need it down the road,

Speaker 2: but you're not going to get it every month.

Speaker 1: It freezes it out for you.

Speaker 2: That way you can call us to freeze it for another half year if you want

Speaker 1: or call us to receive it sooner.

Speaker 2: So what are you saying?

Speaker 1: Like you won't send anymore?

Speaker 2: Yeah, it will be frozen out.

Speaker 1: So it will be a six-month hold on all orders.

Speaker 2: It will freeze the prescription.

Speaker 1: It will remain active just in case you end up wanting them down the road.

Speaker 2: But you don't receive it every month.

Speaker 1: All right, so the next time I do need them, I would have to call you, correct?

Speaker 2: Yeah, you just call us up.

Speaker 1: All right, that's what I want.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I'll go ahead and change over to the six-month freeze plan,

Speaker 1: and you're all set.

Speaker 2: Do you have any questions?

Speaker 1: Appreciate it.

Speaker 2: You're all set to go for today.

Speaker 1: Thank you, buddy.

Speaker 2: Appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Of course.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye now.

Speaker 1: Bye.
